硕士学位论文

面向企业网络的自适应访问控制机制研究

摘 要
云计算、物联网的快速发展，极大地促进了数据交换和信息互联。各种网络应用 技术和网络基础设施的发展，使得信息资源在企业网络中的整合和交互也呈现出了爆 炸式的增长。云计算、物联网等技术也被广泛地应用到企业信息系统的部署与架构中， 在提升了企业网络灵活性的同时，也给企业网络中的数据安全带来了新的挑战。
全新的计算模式和数据处理方式使企业网络环境具有了动态化、复杂化的特点， 使得传统网络安全技术在数据的保护和共享方面起到了至关重要的作用，访问控制技 术作为其核心技术之一，可以通过限制用户的访问范围和访问能力，保护数据不被非 法访问和越权访问。然而在动态且复杂的企业网络环境下，现有的访问控制技术缺乏 自适应调整访问策略的能力，难以提供全面、灵活的资源保护，对于信息安全的保障 具有一定的滞后性，具体体现在：一方面，访问控制策略的制定和维护高度依赖于人 工，管理员需要持续地为新的资源制定访问策略，难以自动化地实现新资源到主体权 限的分配；另一方面，访问控制技术缺乏对内部人员越权的约束，当内部人员实施恶 意行为时，无法自适应地调整主体的权限。针对以上问题，本文对企业网络下自适应 的访问控制机制进行了深入的研究，主要工作和贡献如下：
1. 本文设计了面向企业网络的自适应访问控制系统模型。该系统模型包含两个组 件：访问控制策略生成和评估组件以及面向自适应访问控制的内部异常检测组件。前 者件主要实现了新资源到主体权限的自动化分配；后者根据主体的历史行为，实现主 体到资源权限的自动化调整。两个组件能够在系统运行期间自动化地进行策略调整， 避免了人工干预，提高了访问控制系统的自适应性。
2. 本文提出了一种基于机器学习的访问控制策略生成和评估方案。通过在访问控 制策略挖掘中引入了“资源相似度”的概念，提出了基于资源相似度的策略挖掘算法。 针对新策略的质量评估，提出了一种访问策略评估算法。最后，本文基于真实的亚马 逊访问数据集进行了实验，结果表明提出的策略生成算法和策略评估算法能够有效地 挖掘访问控制策略并删除低质量的策略。
3. 本文提出了一种基于深度学习面向自适应访问控制的内部异常检测方案。本文 使用深度学习方法构建内部异常检测模型，并将其整合到访问控制模型中。特别地， 检测结果将作为访问控制的主体历史行为要素，用于自适应地调整内部人员的访问权 限和范围。本文在 CMU-CERT 数据集上进行了实验，实验结果表明了方法的有效性。
关键词：自适应访问控制，策略动态维护，内部威胁，机器学习，深度学习
I

Abstract

硕士学位论文

Abstract
The rapid development of cloud computing and the Internet of Things has greatly promoted data exchange and information interconnection. With the growth of various network application technologies and network infrastructure, the integration and interaction of information resources in enterprise networks has also shown explosive growth. Cloud computing, Internet of Things and other technologies are widely used in the deployment and architecture of enterprise information systems, which not only improves the flexibility of enterprise network, but also brings new challenges to the data security.
Because of the new computing mode and data processing mode, the enterprise network environment becomes dynamic and complex. The traditional network security technologies play a vital role in data protection and sharing. As one of its core technologies, access control can protect data from illegal access and unauthorized access by limiting the access range and capabilities. However, in a dynamic and complex enterprise network environment, the current access control technology lacks the ability to adaptively adjust access policies, and it is unable to provide comprehensive and flexible resource protection. On the one hand, the formulation and maintenance of access control policies are highly dependent on manual labor. Administrators need to continuously formulate access policies for new resources, and it is difficult to automatically construct policy for new resources. On the other hand, the current access control models fail to restrict the access behavior of internal person. If the insider implements malicious behavior, they cannot adaptively adjust the permission of the resource. To address the above problems, this paper studies the adaptive access control mechanism in enterprise network. The main work and contributions are as follows:
1. This paper designs an adaptive access control system model for enterprise networks. The system model includes two components: an access control policy generation and evaluation component and an internal anomaly detection component for adaptive access control. The former mainly realizes the automatic policy formulation of new resources; the latter realizes the automatic adjustment of the permission of the subject to the resource according to the historical behavior of the subject. The two components can automatically adjust the policy during system operation without manual intervention, and improve the adaptability of the access control system.
2. This paper proposes a scheme for generating and evaluating access control policies based on machine learning. By introducing the concept of "resource similarity" in access
II

硕士学位论文

面向企业网络的自适应访问控制机制研究

control policy mining, and propose a policy mining algorithm based on resource similarity. To evaluate newly generated policy, a policy evaluation algorithm is proposed. Finally, this paper conducts experiments based on real Amazon access data sets. The results show that the proposed policy generation algorithm and policy evaluation algorithm can effectively mine access control policies and delete low-quality policies.
3. This paper proposes an internal anomaly detection scheme based on deep learning for adaptive access control. Our work uses deep learning methods to build an internal anomaly detection model and integrate it into the access control model. In particular, the detection result will be used as the main historical behavior element of access control to adaptively adjust the access permission and scope of internal personnel. We conduct experiments on CMU-CERT dataset, and the experimental results show the effectiveness of the proposed scheme.

Key word: Adaptive access control, Dynamic policy maintenance, Insider threats, Machine
learning, Deep learning

